SOA vs MicroServices:

Microservices evolved from SOA. Share many characteristics

Service oriented intigration

App a 		| App B 		| App F 3rd Party propritory
  |				|					|
  \/			\/					\/
------------------------------------------------
			Enterprise Service Bus
-------------------------------------------------

Service-Oriented Intigration(SOI). Applications communicate with each other through common intigration layer standards SOAP/XML 
over HTTP or JMS. 
OESB. 
OSB deeply rooted into their products. 
Either write heavy orchestration logic in the ESB layer or the
business logic itself in the service bus. 
All enterprise level services are deployed and accessed via ESB.
For such organisations Microservices are altogether different from 
SOA. 
